New World Resources Declines Fourth Day to Lowest in Two Weeks

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-06-22T11:48:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/new-world-resources-declines-fourth-day-to-lowest-in-two-weeks.html
New World Resources Plc, the
largest Czech producer of coking coal, dropped for a fourth
day in  Prague  trading to its lowest level in more than two
weeks.  The stock slid as much as 2.3 percent to 242.3, its
weakest since June 6, and stood down 1.7 percent as of 1:40
p.m. in Prague, extending its declines this week to 4.4
percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  